Text: Monta Ellis released from hospital this a.m. after suffering Grade 2 concussion in last night's game. Will miss final two games of season.
Full recap and highlights of tonight's game. Warriors will be back at home for Fan Appreciation Night on Wednesday. http://ow.ly/4xhBs
Ellis will not travel with the team to Denver for tomorrow's game.
Monta Ellis will be taken to a local hospital for further examination after hitting his head late in tonight's game.
The Warriors wind up on the losing end of a 104-103 contest vs. Sacramento. D. Lee finished w/ 24pts/14rebs. Curry had 27 pts/8assts/6rebs
Just under 3 minutes to play. Warriors trail the Kings 97-95 as Monta nails a jumper.
David Lee now has 37 double-doubles on the year, and tonight marks his 3rd straight 20-point/10-rebound game.
Warriors lead the Kings 83-77 at the end of the third quarter. D. Lee (22 points/10 rebounds) has another double-double. S. Curry has 20.
Halftime at Oracle Arena. Warriors trail the Kings 60-59. D. Wright leads all scorers with 17. D. Lee has 16 points & 7 rebounds.
At the end of the first quarter, the Warriors trail the Kings 30-26.  Stephen Curry has 9 points, Ekpe Udoh has 5 points & 3 rebounds.
David Lee suffered a laceration on his lower lip. Stitches were not needed and he will return.

At the end of the 1st quarter, the Warriors trail the Jazz 23-20. David Lee has 7 points, Monta Ellis has 6.

Text: Full recap of last night's 121-113 overtime defeat: http://ow.ly/3MpQ3
The Warriors were unable to hold off the Bobcats in overtime, falling 121-113. S. Curry had 27 points. M. Ellis & D. Wright had 21 each.
Tied 101-101 at the end of regulation, we're headed for OT. Stephen Curry scored 13 of his 24 points in the 4th & is 8-12 from the floor.
Steph Curry hits another 3. Now has 13 points in the 4th quarter. Warriors lead 98-90 with 1:30 to play.
End of the 3rd, Warriors lead 76-71. All five starters in double figures. Biedrins has 10 points & 12 rebs., Udoh has 7 & 3 off the bench.
Halftime. Warriors lead Charlotte 50-44. S. Curry leads a balanced attack with 11 points. A. Biedrins has 6 points & 9 rebs.
Warriors lead the Bobcats 28-22 at the end of the 1st. Stephen Curry  has 9 points. Andris Biedrins has 4 points & 6 rebounds.
Tonight's starters: GSW - Curry, Ellis, D. Wright, Lee, Biedrins  |  CHA - Augustin, Jackson, Walllace, Diaw, Brown
